Pinus ponderosa

   [2545.jpg]
   Authority Dougl.
   Family Pinopsida:Pinaceae
   Synonyms
   Common names Ponderosa pine, Western pine, Western yellow pine,
   California white pine, foothills yellow pine, Sierra brownbark pine,
   heavy pine, pin jaune, heavy-wooded pine, pinheiro Ponderosa
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 2545

   Notes
   DESCRIPTION: It is an evergreen, coniferous tree reaching a height of
   25-30 m. USE: It provides the most timber of all American pines and, in
   total annual production, is second only to Douglas-fir (Pseudotsuga
   menziesii). The wood is rather light and soft and is used for plywood,
   paneling, mill products, toys, furniture and many other products. The
   tree is used for ornamental and conservation plantings. GROWING PERIOD:
   Perennial. COMMON NAMES: Ponderosa pine. FURTHER INF: Scientific
   synonym: P. arizonica. Ponderosa pine can in tropical and subtropical
   regions be found at elevations from sea level to 3000 m. The
   latitudinal range of natural occurrence is 23-35°N and the tree can be
   found between 23-52°N. The tree is shade tolerant in youth, fire and
   drought resistant, windfirm and tolerant of calcareous soils. Annual
   wood production potential is 5-20 m3/ha. The tree is frost resistant.

   Sources
   SOURCES P. ponderosa Dougl. (22.05.02) E2545
   Webb D 1984 pp 227 [RAIN, TEMP, TEXT, PH, DRA, DEP, LIG, KTMP, USE]
   INSPIRE species 144 [RAIN, TEMP, TEXT, PH, DRA, DEP, LIG, USE]

